    <Feat>
      <Name>Alchemical Spellcasting</Name>
      <Description>Alchemists have a unique way of combining their spells as they cast them.
As an alchemist, your spells are each associated with a different Primer:
Crimsonite, Gildleaf, or Ceruleite. Casting a spell from a single Primer and then
casting a spell from a different Primer will activate a Reaction depending on the
Primer of the spells cast. Reactions come in three variants: Pyrite, Verudite, or
Orchidium. You can only have be in one Reaction at a time, and casting an Alchemist
spell from a Primer not associated with that Reaction will cancel the Reaction.

Casting a Crimsonite spell and then a Gildleaf, or a Gildleaf spell and then a
Crimsonite spell will active a Pyrite Reaction.

Casting a Gildleaf spell and then a Ceruleite spell, or a Ceruleite spell and then a
Gildleaf spells will activate a Verdanite Reaction.

